<paragraph blockId="36.[168,778,1816,1977]" pageId="36" pageNumber="543">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[168,330,1816,1840]" pageId="36" pageNumber="543">Identification.</emphasis>
Perennial tussock grass, 
<quantity box="[658,778,1816,1840]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="36" pageNumber="543" unit="cm" value="60.0" valueMax="70.0" valueMin="50.0">50–70 cm</quantity>
height. Leaf-blades lanceolate with trichomes on the margin, 
<quantity box="[261,368,1885,1909]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.65" metricValueMax="2.3" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="36" pageNumber="543" unit="cm" value="16.5" valueMax="23.0" valueMin="10.0">10–23 cm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[438,560,1885,1909]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="36" pageNumber="543" unit="cm" value="0.35" valueMax="0.4" valueMin="0.3">0.3–0.4 cm</quantity>
wide, ligulate. Distinguished by its open panicle, 
<quantity box="[508,601,1919,1943]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="0.8" pageId="36" pageNumber="543" unit="cm" value="11.5" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="8.0">8–15 cm</quantity>
long with verticillate branches.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="36" pageNumber="543" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="36.[168,777,1993,2051]" pageId="36" pageNumber="543">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[168,279,1993,2017]" pageId="36" pageNumber="543">Remarks.</emphasis>
Relatively common species on the native grassland, occurring mainly over shallow soils.
</paragraph>
